.TH "regulator_set_current_limit_regmap" 9 "regulator_set_current_limit_regmap" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
regulator_set_current_limit_regmap \- set_current_limit for regmap users
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" regulator_set_current_limit_regmap
.BI "(struct regulator_dev *rdev "  ","
.BI "int min_uA "  ","
.BI "int max_uA "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "rdev" 12
regulator to operate on
.IP "min_uA" 12
Lower bound for current limit
.IP "max_uA" 12
Upper bound for current limit
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Regulators that use regmap for their register I/O can set curr_table,
csel_reg and csel_mask fields in their descriptor and then use this
as their set_current_limit operation, saving some code.
